Different methods for 3D PC-MRA data generation from 4D Flow CMR have been proposed and evaluated [4–6]. These methods combine and average the velocity and magnitude information over the cardiac cycle. The velocities yield higher intensities in the resulting image in areas of high blood flow, while the magnitude signal adds morphological information and mitigates noise in areas of very low signal, such as the lungs. For N timeframes, [3, 5], and [7], proposed the following equation:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
